name: Southwest Cowling! WestJet 737-7CT [C-FKIW] Takeoff from Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
I'm not entirely sure when, but at some point in the last two weeks, clearly this WestJet 737-700 needed an engine cowling while somewhere in the US, and I guess Southwest had one handy. This bird has been flying around with it for over a week now, and surprisingly, it hasn't been changed back. Enjoy this quick video of what some spotters have dubbed "SouthWestJet"! ATC included.

Thanks for watching!
